<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-02-09T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-02-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="263" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d263">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">835.73/133: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">White</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-02-09T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February 9,
                                        1922—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>4. Your No. 8, February 7, 4 p.m.</p>
                        <p>Your action approved.</p>
                        <p>Department informed by local representative of Western Union and of
                            Western Telegraph Company that appropriate instructions to make
                            necessary corrections on both points mentioned by you will be sent
                            immediately to Oldham.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>